-- Northwest Air unsecured claims may get 66-83 pct
-- 
-- Thu Feb 15, 2007 1:10pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/15/us-northwest-disclosure-idUSN1538732420070215

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Bankrupt Northwest Airlines Corp. NWACQ.PK said  on Thursday that holders of general unsecured claims would receive stock valued at between 66 percent to 83 percent of allowed claims when the company exits Chapter 11. 


 The No. 5 U.S. carrier said in a filing in the U.S. Bankruptcy Court for the Southern District of New York that it remains on track to leave bankruptcy in the second quarter of 2007 and that its employees will have an equivalent of 20 percent economic interest in the airline